rComments: I absolutely loved Saba even though our course didnt have formal meetings. You can just tell by her weekly posts and podcasts that she in an inspirational educator. I learned a lot about racism and anti-racism in education and the readings she selected were relevant and engaging. The book report at the end was the cherry on top to this course

I had read good reviews on her and she is a nice person, but I was disappointed in this class. She gave a list of readings, gave three assignments but was extraordinarily vague. There were no lectures and no guidance until after she graded the papers giving it very much a "I know it when I see it vibe." Also, yes, very focused on a particular issue

I absolutely adored this class. It was probably my favourite course of my Masters program. Her podcasts were super interesting and she always included different multimedia in her weekly tasks. I appreciated the *diversity*!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: You won't regret taking a course with Dr. Alvi! She is extremely dedicated to creating an inclusive learning environment where all voices are heard and differences and diversity are celebrated and encouraged. She has created a curriculum that not only engages but also supports different learning abilities. Such a caring & fantastic professor!

It is revitalizing to see educators that are truly invested in our educational journey and growth as a human being. Saba is such an amazing educator and encourages her students to do better and continuously provides tools and mechanisms for their ongoing success. By far, one of my all-time favourite professors in the Faculty of Education!!

Professor Alvi was amazing, easily the best professor I had in the Faculty of Education. She was thought-provoking and a true inspiration, the teaching material was very relevant, as her students we were given many opportunities to show our work and do well in the class. Her feedback was very useful. I 100% recommend her!

Professor Alvi is extremely knowledgeable and passionate about her work. Her lectures are captivating and the course material is relevant and well thought out. She is approachable, organized & professional and truly cares about making sure her students are successful. She was one of the best professors Ive had and I would highly recommend!

I loved having her as a prof. She is not only well versed in the realm of education but makes me feel seen as a student. She is approachable and kind and most importantly respectful. Had her multiple times in my two-year program and learned so much from her.

Great Professor. Down to earth, approachable, resourceful and most importantly... knowledgable! Saba did a fantastic job tackling a very tough subject area. Teaching social justice in any capacity is no easy feat but Saba was awesome!

Saba is an excellent professor. Her ability to facilitate and lecture are captivating, in addition to the fact that she is able to engage her students in critical thinking. Many teacher candidates are used to getting easy grades, but Saba makes you work for it. You really have to be insightful and thorough to do well, but it is worth the effort.

Pure disappointment. Very narrow-minded and clearly has no experience teaching. not capable to discuss ideas or to consider opposing views. She teaches things she doesn't practice. Avoid if you can :(

I have taken a few (mandatory) courses with Prof Alvi and have mixed feelings about her. She is very disorganized, takes a long time to mark and does not provide a lot of feedback. The course also failed to address any topics beyond race. In my opinion a course on inclusivity should cover disability issues, gender, sexuality, etc.

Honestly I was super disappointed by this professor. She appears to be very passionate about the subject manner. However, I found her to be very unwilling to actually go into depth about some of the concepts discussed in class. She was not willing to answer questions or maintain open a dialogue about certain topics she discussed.

The course was indigenous fem so it would have been nice to have a prof of indig heritage but prof alvi handled the situation so graciously. she even brought in indigenous women speakers to share their knowledge, which was a wise choice. she treated the subject matter w sensitivity and was very good at conveying the material. i learned a lot

I liked this class! I felt like the papers were hard, but I got an OK mark considering these were the first papers I've written since 1st year. She's very approachable, there are harsh penalties and make-ups for missing class,but class is interesting anyways so I always showed up! Many guest speakers. Very respectful of the subject matter.

Not a bad prof. Pretty reasonable in her expectations. Lots of guest speakers. I would definitely take a course with her again, but I wouldnt go out of my way to have her as a prof. Shes good though. I learnt a lot in her class. Final was a take home and readings were online which are both a big bonus.

Great prof, kept the class interesting with relevant and up to date info on emerging issues. I enjoyed every single class, and the discussions were great. Prof. Alvi is very approachable, wish more profs were like this. Really appreciated her feedback and availability to get to back to me when I had a question. Highly recommended.

I enjoyed all my classes with Prof. Alvi, I've taken two courses with her and both were taught with immense interest, knowledge, relevance and passion. Her classes were enjoyable and there was always a chance for class discussions. I strongly recommend taking a course with prof. Alvi. She provided great feedback whenever I needed it.
Saba is a down to Earth professor, super cool, funny and knowledgeable. She's very sexy too! It's always nice to have a good professor who also looks great!

She is one of the most down to earth profs that I've had in all my years of school. She is very knowledgeable about her subject matter and its practical applications in the field. I found her to be quite approachable and absolutely practices what she preaches. Despite the group work in the class, I always felt treated like an individual.
I couldn't imagine this course being taught by anyone else! By far my favourite course and prof this semester. Sad the term is over :(
Great Prof!

I enjoyed this class. The prof taught us to critically think about issues & not just depend on the theories we read. She included a lot of class discussion that isn't easy with a class of 120. It gave us a chance to share our opinions. She grades hard but if you go see her in her office she is very helpful/nice & my grades went up with each paper.

The prof didn't really teach anything in this course. Most classes she would briefly talk about the readings, then we would have a class discussion for an hour. The take home essay questions were given to us in the last class, and it was due half a week later..... Why not during the exam period? Wouldn't recommend this course/prof

She seems like a great prof and a nice person, but she hardly ever lectured! On the rare occasion that she DID, she usually asked us to engage in class discussions or watch films. We learned very little from her! The assignments SEEMED easy, but were marked REALLY HARSHLY-You can't ask for an A+ analysis/paper..when you haven't taught us anything.

This was a very interesting class, however the TA's lectured very often - when the TA's made lectures confusing.  There were 2 Reading Reviews, a blog assignment and a take home final exam which was an essay.  If you are not a strong writer, this isn't the class for you. Since there was no mid term or final exam their was no reason to go to class.
